  "en_snotes_asad": "I.e., His Being is eternal, without anything preceding His existence and without anything outlasting its infinity: an interpretation given by the Prophet himself, as recorded in several well-authenticated Traditions. Thus, \"time\" itself - a concept beyond man's understanding - is but God's creation. I.e., He is the transcendental Cause of all that exists and, at the same time, immanent in every phenomenon of His creation - cf. the oft-repeated Qur'anic phrase (e.g., in verse S), \"all things go back unto God [as their source]\"; in the words of Tabari, \"He is closer to everything than anything else could be\". Another - perhaps supplementary - rendering could be, \"He is the Evident as well as the Hidden\": i.e., \"His existence is evident (zahir) in the effects of His activity, whereas He Himself is not perceptible (ghayr mudrak) to our senses\" (Zamakhshari).",
